===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# A [[Hindu]] [[pilgrimage]].
#* {{quote-book|en|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=JPeQ7Vf6hYwC&pg=PA261&dq=yatra|page=261|title=The Saffron Wave: Democracy and Hindu Nationalism in Modern India|author=Thomas Blom Hansen|publisher|publisher=Princeton University Press|year=1999|ISBN=9780691006710}}
#*: Thousands of activists and vehicles therefore diffused quietly out of Delhi in the following days to reassemble in a '''yatra''' that now swelled to 40–50,000 people.
#* {{quote-book|en|page=80|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=qWMbQI5BkXwC&pg=PT94&dq=yatra|title=Lighting the Lamp of Wisdom: a Week Inside a Yoga Ashram|author=John Ittner|publisher=SkyLight Paths Publishing|year=2002|ISBN=9781893361522}}
#*: By calling this little stroll a '''''yatra''''' I am making a mild joke to myself, because in India a '''''yatra''''' can be a grueling expedition such as a hike to the top of Mount Kailas in the Himalayas.
#* {{quote-book|en|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=2-wsjaChM_QC&pg=PA71&dq=yatra|page=71|title=Contemporary Society: Identity, Intervention and Ideology in Tribal India and Beyond|volume=7|editor=Georg Pfeffer|chapter=Forts and Camps in Tribal Orissa: Kshatriyaization and Industrialization Compared|author=Christian Strümpell|publisher=Concept Publishing Company|year=2005|ISBN=9788180695346}}
#*: At the inauguration of this temple a '''yatra''' for her was performed attracting again a big part of Chatamput's mostly female inhabitants, who all claimed that Kondamakalamma now is the "real" goddess of the village.
#* {{quote-book|en|title=Ritual and Identity: Performative Practices as Effective Transformations of Social Reality|volume=8|publisher=LIT Verlag Berlin-Hamburg-Münster|year=2006|ISBN=9783825880422|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=BkBh1Nl4dHwC&pg=PA287&dq=yatra|page=287}}
#*: I thus wonder whether the '''yatra''' was not primarily "efficient" for the upper middle classes who - physically removed from direct participation - enjoyed the BJP going on a '''yatra''', presenting them with ready-made edutainment about nationality, easy to digest, without much physical and mental effort.
